I reject Led Zeppelin I here not because it lacks merit — it shares important traits like analogue warmth, room ambience and punch — but because its guitar‑and‑vocal forward presentation is less compatible with my emphasis on subtle stereo detail, instrument separation and textural refinement. The urgent upfront vocals and riff‑centric midrange focus tend to push performance immediacy over the nuanced, instrument‑forward mastering and micro‑detail that I prioritize for collector‑style, front‑to‑back listening.

